From: Octopus Orchestrator upstream PR draft wave (M0-15)
Subject: [PATCH] gateway: register octo.* methods in server-methods-list

Advertise Octopus Orchestrator method names from the canonical
Gateway method directory. Names are singly-sourced in
src/octo/wire/methods.ts as OCTO_METHOD_NAMES; this change spreads
them into BASE_METHODS so listGatewayMethods() returns them.

Runtime feature-flag gating (octo.enabled) is enforced at dispatch
time per OCTO-DEC-027, not at listing time — matching the existing
pattern where method names are listed regardless of whether their
subsystems are currently configured on.

No behavior change for deployments with octo.enabled: false (default
through Milestone 1).

Draft authored against upstream commit 9ece252.

---
 src/gateway/server-methods-list.ts | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/gateway/server-methods-list.ts b/src/gateway/server-methods-list.ts
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/src/gateway/server-methods-list.ts
+++ b/src/gateway/server-methods-list.ts
@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@
 import { listChannelPlugins } from "../channels/plugins/index.js";
+import { OCTO_METHOD_NAMES } from "../octo/wire/methods.js";
 import { GATEWAY_EVENT_UPDATE_AVAILABLE } from "./events.js";

 const BASE_METHODS = [
@@ -124,6 +125,8 @@ const BASE_METHODS = [
   "chat.history",
   "chat.abort",
   "chat.send",
+  // Octopus Orchestrator control plane (see src/octo/wire/methods.ts).
+  ...OCTO_METHOD_NAMES,
 ];

 export function listGatewayMethods(): string[] {
